<font color="#FF0000">A PERSPECTIVE</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jun  3 22:50:47 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Art, you are right, it is one hell of a see-saw and I did not come to this conclusion easily. If you can, try to look it through my eyes, as a medic. I have taken the unpopular stand of supporting our country's effort in Bosnia, Haiti, and Somolia. In all circumstances it did not work as well as I wish it did, but I supported these endevours because of the kids. To me, it's all about the kids. By the time we got into Bosnia, a quarter million were dead. It is my hope that the troops being in Bosnia saved at least that many should we not have interceeded. I am willing to give them that credit and honor them for that contribution!<br><br>
In Vietnam, again, to me it's about the kids. I am no closed eye bleeding heart liberal, as you know me better. Nor am I am a &quot;nuke 'em dead&quot; type. I don't doubt that this is all about money. It is my hope that some of it trickles to the right places and that, as Andy says, we can have some inpact in regards to human rights.<br><br>
My best to you, Art!
